1. Software architecture
  ** System architecture
    1. Buying customer browses items (can look in general, or filter by prices, or by categories, or by proximity) and selects an item. 
    2. Buying customer messages selling customer for more details.Message goes from sender’s device to the backend to the receiver’s device. 
    3. Negotiating and sale (afterwards) happens.
    4. Selling customer unlists item.
    5. Request is sent to the backend and processed. 
    6. Update item availability in the database.
    7. Update frontend.
